Requirements:
  -- Web Server (e.g. Apache)
  -- Database Server ( MySQL ) 
  -- PHP 
  -- Git ( http://git-scm.com )
  For more information, go to http://drupal.org/requirements
  
Build the project:
1. git clone https://github.com/bhle/bhle
2. git checkout drupal-dev
3. import bhle/portal/drupal/database/bhle_portal_dev.sql to your mysql databse
4. change the file name of bhle/portal/drupal/www/sites/default/ref.settings.php to settings.php;
   modify the $database array with your database information.
5. modify bhle/.git/info/exclude file, add settings.php at the end
Now your drupal portal project should be ok to run on your web browser

Contribute to the project:
1. after build the project successfully, 
   git checkout drupal-dev
   git checkout -b your-own-branch-name-here
2. do all modifications you want to add to this project, and test to be sure everything is ok
3. git checkout drupal-dev
4. git pull 
   if pull success, go to step 5
   if there are conflicts:
   1) roll back to the original drupal-dev you pulled last time
   2) git pull again, to have all new modifications from other developers
   3) go back to step 2, and do all again
5. git checkout your-own-branch-name-here
6. git add *
7. git commit -m "your commit message"
8. git rebase drupal-dev your-own-branch-name-here
10. git checkout drupal-dev
11. git merge your-own-branch-name-here
12. git push (you should have a username and password to be able to do this)
